      "type": "text",
      "content": "The team wants to do some deep dive into a subset of borrowers and their loans. Identify from 1.11.2026 Habor Capital Final.pdf: the two most risk concentrated sectors (slide 3) and the first month (month X) when High risk (D) and Distressed (F) loans combined expand beyond 50% (slide 6). Filter from enriched_loan_data.csv data since month X (inclusive) till the end of 2024 for borrowers: (1) in the two high risk sectors, (2) whose expected loss for month X requires VP approval, and (3) whose delinquency bucket status worsened in month X compared to month X-1. Risk framework and definitions are documented in Executive Documentation - Harbor Capital Risk Dashboard.docx. Export those data into a new excel file named enrich_loan_data_subset.xlsx. Create a pivot table in a new sheet named \"Summary\" and summarise the \"Loss_Balance_Ratio\" by Month_Key (row). Filter in the pivot table for borrowers that have been in business for more than 5 years and are of Variable interest type. \"Loss_Balance_Ratio\" is defined as the ratio between total expected loss and total current balance. Round the numbers to 3 decimal points. Use formulas directly in the sheets so the pivot table can update seamlessly when the data changes."
    }
